Allows to edit a javascript file in Emacs and to have the same kind of interactivity as you do with the Shell or when developing in Emacs with Python or SlimeMode -- ie it allows you to send javascript code from an emacs buffer inside
Firefox. (Mozilla?)

See:
[http://the.unwashedmeme.com/blog/2005/06/02/javascript-shellserver-for-emacs/ Javascript ShellServer for Emacs]

Based on 
[http://mozdev.org/pipermail/conkeror/2004-November/000014.html emacs slave]
